Detailed Description

Provides methods for accessing the display in a generic way. For the application developer it is recommended to use the class DeviceContext for drawing operations. Using the display device directly is possible but it is important to know, that this approach bypasses the APOXI window system.

void DefaultDisplay::OnTimer (   ) 
 

Is invoked if the backlight or power has been timed out (see Display::SetBacklightTimeout and Display::SetPowerTimeout). The method should not invoked directly by the MMI and is public only to keep backward compatibility with older APOXI versions.

void DefaultDisplay::OnTimer (   ) 
 

Obsolete - is provided for backward compatibility with earlier APOXI releases. The display device does not do any timer handling, this should be done by the MMI.

virtual void DefaultDisplay::Refresh (  const CustomFrameBuffer *  custom_frame_buf  )  [virtual]
 

Refreshs the display area specified by the blitting-rectangle (see Display::SetBlitRect and Display::GetBlitRect). Whether the refreshing is done synchronous or asynchronous, depends on the capabilities of the low-level display device. Per default APOXI does not block when refreshing the display, hence block is set to FALSE. If the update should be done synchronous, set block to TRUE and APOXI will wait until the low-level display device has finished the refreshing.

Parameters:
custom_frame_buf Optional parameter which allows to pass a custom frame buffer for refreshing instead of using the internal frame buffer.
